<li id="cite_note-28"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFPhilip_Gibbs.2C_Jim_Carr_and_Don_Koks2008">Philip Gibbs, Jim Carr and Don Koks (2008). <a href="http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/physics/Relativity/SR/mass.html" class="external text" title="http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/physics/Relativity/SR/mass.html" rel="nofollow">"What is relativistic mass?"</a>. <i>Usenet Physics FAQ</i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/physics/Relativity/SR/mass.html" class="external free" title="http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/physics/Relativity/SR/mass.html" rel="nofollow">http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/physics/Relativity/SR/mass.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-09-19</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=What+is+relativistic+mass%3F&amp;rft.atitle=Usenet+Physics+FAQ&amp;rft.aulast=Philip+Gibbs%2C+Jim+Carr+and+Don+Koks&amp;rft.au=Philip+Gibbs%2C+Jim+Carr+and+Don+Koks&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fmath.ucr.edu%2Fhome%2Fbaez%2Fphysics%2FRelativity%2FSR%2Fmass.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Special_relativity"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Note that in 2008 the last editor, Don Koks, rewrote a significant portion of the page, changing it from a view extremely dismissive of the usefulness of relativistic mass to one which hardly questions it. The previous version was: <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFPhilip_Gibbs_and_Jim_Carr1998">Philip Gibbs and Jim Carr (1998). <a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20070630144936/http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/physics/Relativity/SR/mass.html" class="external text" title="http://web.archive.org/web/20070630144936/http://math.ucr.edu/home/baez/physics/Relativity/SR/mass.html" rel="nofollow">"Does mass change with speed?"</a>. <i>Usenet Physics FAQ</i>. Archi